            <article class="post-76235 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-education category-food-and-drink" id="post-76235">
  <header class="entry-header">

          <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2019/06/model-this-spoiled-rich-kids-edition.html">Model this (spoiled rich kids edition)</a></h2>
    
      <div class="byline">
        by&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="author"><a href="/about">Tyler Cowen</a></span>
        <time class="entry-date published" datetime="2019-06-27 14:28:10">June 27, 2019 at 2:28 pm </time>
                            in
          <ul class="entry-tags">
                                        <li class="tag" rel="tag"><a href="https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/category/education">Education</a></li>
                                                      <li class="tag" rel="tag"><a href="https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/category/food-and-drink">Food and Drink</a></li>
                                    </ul><!-- /.entry-tags -->
                        </div><!-- /.byline -->
  </header><!-- /.entry-header -->
  <div class="entry-content">
    <div class="pf-content"><div>From the <a href="https://secure-web.cisco.com/1bT076-nYG58Gxe8G5phTFUYP6Ck3ZIyUrhPCBAVeh76c6uMz2bVTnJcLA2SWhvOnfS0Jrre5S7txMDcaP8xiKbuNYgbgj3sj7QpDrR9S-h3rj7eadMpDhjydPDvWAnBf0AI9RB-SZiQLZf1Ru3QXcEF7T7J7XwArET5OwA-J7JqyNsKoI7LrhjpYqmZc6CJlBdUdrCIf1Qj53icjxJUwCer0THFR8ywq8O3izLbqjlezLvXyJh5YHzAOUGrjn5HS2rQ4NJlod-C7-K78rQxyjv1ApKlcbVnaI9RoMXrDZXWZI0W9foOUXW042KLUktrXiHrkzsD2O5R0BivFRfe0r6JwauRwYsj-grmc2smOQOV0aakbBMkF7QbzFIFaNkq8HTVwSqx7MpDQnskM5UH_ASqAiZBnvfm-7_WASFgXf45awqPMtelPPxKRupSnbLKfnKQSRJ0YJhRQDB1s3MNCPw/https%3A%2F%2Ffeatures.thecrimson.com%2F2017%2Fsenior-survey%2Flifestyle-narrative%2F" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-auth="NotApplicable">Harvard Class of 2017 senior survey</a>:</div>
<div>
<ul>
<li>&#8220;About 80 percent of respondents reported drinking alcohol at least two or three times a month, and 39 percent reported drinking at least twice a week.&#8221; (60% reported drinking once a week or more)</li>
<li>&#8220;Students who came from lower-income households were much less likely to drink than their wealthier peers; 35 percent of respondents whose parents make less than $40,000 in combined income drank at least once a week while that figure was 69 percent for students whose parents make at least a combined $250,000.&#8221;</li>
</ul>
<p>Via Tyler R.</p>
</div>
</div>
  </div><!-- /.entry-content -->
